---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const title = 'Best Shopify Email Marketing Apps for Gift Cards in 2026';
const description = 'Compare Shopify email apps for gift-card marketing, gifting moments, recipient journeys, delivery timing, and redemption-aware retention.';
const apps = [['Klaviyo','Gift-card programs with rich data','Useful for purchaser, recipient, value, and redemption segments.','Gift and recipient identity need careful handling.','https://www.klaviyo.com/features/segmentation'],['Omnisend','Commerce teams scaling gifting','A practical fit for gift campaigns, seasonal flows, and coordinated channels.','Promotion and recipient frequency need governance.','https://www.omnisend.com/features/'],['Sequenzy','Focused gift-card education','Good for explaining purchase, delivery, redemption, and the next useful action.','Gift-card event integration should be verified.','https://sequenzy.com/'],['Brevo','Broad gifting campaigns','Useful when gifting messages share a wider campaign and automation stack.','Redemption state may require mapping.','https://www.brevo.com/features/marketing-automation/'],['Shopify Email','Simple native gift-card campaigns','A straightforward option for small stores and seasonal announcements.','Less suited to recipient-aware journeys.','https://www.shopify.com/email-marketing']];
---
<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}><main class="container page-stack"><p class="eyebrow">Shopify email marketing apps</p><h1>{title}</h1><p class="lede">Gift-card email has two audiences: the purchaser and the recipient. A good program helps each person understand what happens next without exposing unnecessary personal or purchase information.</p><p>Measure gift-card purchase, delivery success, redemption, recipient conversion, and support contacts. Separate purchaser reminders from recipient onboarding, and suppress promotional asks when the gift-card experience or redemption has an open issue.</p><h2>Shortlist at a glance</h2><table><thead><tr><th>App</th><th>Best fit</th><th>Strength</th><th>Tradeoff</th></tr></thead><tbody>{apps.map(a=><tr><td>{a[0]}</td><td>{a[1]}</td><td>{a[2]}</td><td>{a[3]}</td></tr>)}</tbody></table>{apps.map(a=><section><h2>{a[0]} for gift cards</h2><p><strong>Best for:</strong> {a[1]}. {a[2]}</p><p><strong>Why it stands out:</strong> {a[0]} is useful when the workflow can distinguish purchaser, recipient, delivered card, redeemed balance, and follow-up opportunity. Keep the operational message clear, provide an easy support path, and avoid turning a gift recipient into a marketing contact without an appropriate permission basis. Redemption-aware messaging is more valuable than another generic offer.</p><table><tbody><tr><th>Pros</th><td>{a[2]}</td></tr><tr><th>Cons</th><td>{a[3]}</td></tr><tr><th>Pricing context</th><td>Check current contacts, sends, automation, and transaction/integration limits; gifting can create additional recipient events.</td></tr><tr><th>Source</th><td><a href={a[4]} rel="nofollow">Official product information</a></td></tr></tbody></table></section>)}<h2>Decision guide</h2><table><thead><tr><th>Need</th><th>Prioritize</th><th>Measure</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Delivery</td><td>Recipient and event state</td><td>Delivery success</td></tr><tr><td>Redemption</td><td>Balance and purchase context</td><td>Redemption rate</td></tr><tr><td>Permission</td><td>Recipient consent controls</td><td>Complaints and opt-outs</td></tr></tbody></table><p>Explore <a href="/alternatives">Shopify alternatives</a>, review <a href="/use-cases/holiday-gifting">holiday-gifting use cases</a>, or browse <a href="/apps">all Shopify email apps</a>.</p></main></BaseLayout>
